remixlab.bias.agent

Class ActionAgent<P extends Profile<?,?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • remixlab.bias.core.Agent
      • remixlab.bias.agent.ActionAgent<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - Profile to parameterize the Agent with.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActionKeyboardAgent, ActionMotionAgent

    public class ActionAgent<P extends Profile<?,?>>
extends Agent
    An ActionAgent is just an Agent holding some Profile s. The Agent uses the Shortcut -> Action mappings defined by each of its Profiles to parse the BogusEvent into an user-defined Action (see handle(BogusEvent)).

    The default implementation here holds only a single Profile (see profile()) attribute (note that we use the type of the Profile to parameterize the ActionAgent). Different profile groups are provided by the ActionMotionAgent, the ActionWheeledMotionAgent and the ActionKeyboardAgent specializations, which roughly represent an HIDevice (like a kinect), a wheeled HIDevice (like a mouse) and a generic keyboard, respectively.

    Third-parties implementations should "simply":

    • Derive from the ActionAgent above that best fits their needs.
    • Supply a routine to reduce application-specific input data into BogusEvents (given them their name).
    • Properly call Agent.updateTrackedGrabber(BogusEvent) and handle(BogusEvent) on them.
    The remixlab.proscene.Scene.ProsceneMouse and remixlab.proscene.Scene.ProsceneKeyboard classes provide good example implementations. Note that the ActionAgent methods defined in this package (bias) should rarely be in need to be overridden, not even handle(BogusEvent).

      • handle

        public void handle(BogusEvent event)
        Overriding of the Agent main method. The profile() is used to parse the event into an user-defined action which is then enqueued as an event-grabber tuple ( Agent.enqueueEventTuple(EventGrabberTuple)), used to instruct the Agent.inputGrabber() the user-defined action to perform.

        Note 1: alienGrabber()s always make the tuple to be enqueued even if the action is null (see Agent.enqueueEventTuple(EventGrabberTuple, boolean)).

        Note 2: This method should be overridden only in the (rare) case the ActionAgent should deal with custom BogusEvents defined by the third-party, i.e., bogus events different than those declared in the remixlab.bias.event package.

        Overrides:
        handle in class Agent
        See Also:
        Agent.inputGrabber()
